    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - DIRECTIONAL BULB REMOVE AND REPLACE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>DIRECTIONAL BULB REMOVE AND REPLACE</title>
        <para>The directional bulbs are located within the headlight module on the underside of the fender assembly. To
            replace the headlight halogen bulb or the amber directional bulb, the hood must be tilted.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Unlatch the hood assembly and tilt the hood to the open position.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the outboard socket cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900856">Figure 56, Item 1</hotlnk>), this will be the directional socket on each side
                of the chassis.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900856" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900856.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Directional Light Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. DIRECTIONAL BULB SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT AND DIRECTIONAL LIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Twist the socket cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900857">Figure 57, Item 1</hotlnk>) to remove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900857" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900857.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Directional Bulb Access</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BULB AND SOCKET ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the socket and bulb assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900857">Figure 57, Item 2</hotlnk>), twist and pull up to remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900858">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900858" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900858.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 58. Directional Bulb Remove/ Install</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AMBER DIRECTIONAL BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB SOCKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900859">Figure 59, Item 2</hotlnk>) or install directional bulb, push downward on
                bulb, twist and lift out.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">to install the directional bulb, insert bulb in socket, push down and twist to lock.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert bulb (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900860">Figure 60, Item 1</hotlnk>) and socket assembly in light housing and twist to
                lock bulb in socket seat.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace socket cover and twist to lock.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900859" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900859.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 59. Directional Bulb Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SOCKET COVER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DIRECTIONAL AMBER BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT HOUSING</callout1>
                <callout1>4. DIRECTION BULB SOCKET AND SEAT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0900860" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900860.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 60. Directional Bulb Replacement</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. AMBER BULB</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB SOCKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. HOUSING BASE AND WIRE CONNECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
